lzh_formatted:
  title: 元校書
  author: 郭㻒
  language: lzh
  text: 今朝展淸眺。詩興屬南山。岸幘發長嘯。始知天地寬。
korean:
  title: 원교서
  author: 곽균
  language: kor
  text: |-
    오늘 아침 펼쳐진 맑은 조망에
    시흥은 남산에 붙였네
    건을 젖혀 쓰고 긴 휘파람 부니
    천지 넓은 줄 비로소 알겠네
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0220_010_0370&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: To the Former School Librarian
  author: Kwak Gyun
  language: eng
  text: |-
    This morning's crystalline vista unfolds—
    my poetic spirit clings to Southern Mountain.
    With hat tilted back, I whistle long and clear,
    and suddenly know the vastness of heaven and earth.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: Southern Mountain (南山) likely refers to Namsan, a sacred peak in Korean geography, often associated with transcendence and clarity of vision in classical poetry
  - key: ''
    value: The gesture of tilting back one's hat while whistling suggests a moment of sudden enlightenment and liberation, a common motif in East Asian contemplative poetry
